    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the red onion and apple have started to soften, add your <strong>star anise</strong>, <strong>cider vinegar</strong>,<strong> </strong>1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong> and 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[75ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [100ml]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>to the pot</p><p>Cook for 8-10 min further or until the apple has started to break down</p><p>Once done, set aside to cool slightly before serving – this is your <strong>spiced apple sauce</strong></p><p>Remove the <strong>star anise</strong> and discard</p>",
